Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into
thin strips.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @penne pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender,
~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{for drizzling} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and sliced pepper.
Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until the chicken is cooked through and the pepper has softened,
~{8-10%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

When the chicken and pepper have 1 min of cooking time left, add the garlic to
the pan and fry until fragrant.

Add the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g},
@chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder),
@sugar{1%tsp} and @water{50%ml} to the pan.

Stir and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly
thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the cooked pasta and @butter{20%g} and half the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Heat until the pasta is piping hot
and the butter has melted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Share the smoky chicken pasta between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese.

Enjoy!